75
00:06:16,610 --> 00:06:18,737
Why don't you change the topic?

76
00:06:18,737 --> 00:06:23,398
If you talk and ask about him again and again, they'd ask you who you are to him.

77
00:06:23,398 --> 00:06:24,538
Hey!

78
00:06:24,538 --> 00:06:26,349
I'm his landlady, mun!

79
00:06:26,349 --> 00:06:27,870
Hush!

80
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:30,531
Sit, now.

81
00:06:30,531 --> 00:06:31,610
Enough! C'mon.

82
00:06:31,610 --> 00:06:33,367
Sit down.

83
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:24,790
... Leaves an impression with his humility, my dear.
-Just mention her name and address.

84
00:07:24,790 --> 00:07:27,140
I'll talk to Dad.
-Love Farah for four months --

85
00:07:27,140 --> 00:07:29,390
What's this balderdash!
-Swear on my life if I'm lying.

86
00:07:29,390 --> 00:07:31,820
Just keep on loving me,
-That's neat.

87
00:07:31,820 --> 00:07:35,370
You're a right emotional man.
-She's just voicing unfounded suspicions!
-The move he's played

88
00:07:35,370 --> 00:07:39,170
Is one I'll never forgive him for!
-What's your wife's name?
-My Afzal has become the best one [Afzal] today!

89
00:07:39,170 --> 00:07:42,010
You've just gotten up, haven't you?
-But he's a first rate fraudster.
-Just a spot of lipstick's got you stunned!

90
00:07:42,010 --> 00:07:44,280
Then why did you take us there?
-How say you tell me -

91
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:46,340
How does this lipstick look?
-Farah is the one who used to write you letters, right?

92
00:07:46,340 --> 00:07:49,810
I'd kept you as an option.
-You'd leave Hyderabad for the one who doesn't love you,

93
00:07:49,810 --> 00:07:51,990
Shoot the bugger!
-She's not the one who used to write letters to me, Mum.

94
00:07:51,990 --> 00:07:54,600
The job as a security guard, you know...
-And you'd leave those who love you

95
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:57,060
In Hyderabad?
-'My Afzal'

96
00:07:57,060 --> 00:07:58,790
'Has become a great man'.
-Spit in my face if I lose.

97
00:07:58,790 --> 00:08:02,160
10,000 a month, and loving Farah Ibrahim!
-Just don't do that

98
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:06,430
Which you would be ashamed to do.
-Proposals will line up once Wali's out of the picture, you'll see!

99
00:08:06,430 --> 00:08:09,390
He'd kill me if he got out! What are you waiting for? Shoot the bugger!

100
00:08:09,390 --> 00:08:11,340
Afzal!

101
00:09:55,860 --> 00:09:57,976
I've offered my prayers.

102
00:09:58,316 --> 00:10:00,216
Now, beseech the Lord

103
00:10:00,216 --> 00:10:03,786
That he be alright.

104
00:10:04,406 --> 00:10:05,844
Who?

105
00:10:06,262 --> 00:10:08,893
Do I have to tell you his name, now?

106
00:10:08,893 --> 00:10:11,373
His name is etched in every breath of yours

107
00:10:11,373 --> 00:10:14,697
And courses through your veins, Lubna.

108
00:10:14,697 --> 00:10:16,148
What happened to him?

109
00:10:16,148 --> 00:10:17,182
There!

110
00:10:17,182 --> 00:10:19,260
Now you know who it is!

111
00:10:19,260 --> 00:10:20,770
Don't worry.

112
00:10:20,770 --> 00:10:22,536
Nothing's happened to him.

113
00:10:22,536 --> 00:10:24,286
I just thought

114
00:10:24,286 --> 00:10:26,819
That may nothing happen to him.

115
00:10:26,819 --> 00:10:28,750
I've prayed for many people,

116
00:10:28,750 --> 00:10:30,740
But when his name came up, I thought

117
00:10:30,740 --> 00:10:35,826
The most effective prayers for him would come from your heart.

118
00:10:38,110 --> 00:10:40,266
What did you think?

119
00:10:40,266 --> 00:10:43,120
And why did you think that may nothing happen to him?

120
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:44,686
Why are you on the rack?

121
00:10:44,686 --> 00:10:46,837
Beseech the Lord if you've already offered you prayers

122
00:10:46,837 --> 00:10:47,756
That

123
00:10:47,756 --> 00:10:49,706
May the Lord will that he be fine.

124
00:10:49,706 --> 00:10:52,616
In fact, you should keep praying for him.

125
00:10:52,616 --> 00:10:53,670
I said it

126
00:10:53,670 --> 00:10:54,900
Because it just occurred to me,

127
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:55,370
'Alright',

128
00:10:55,370 --> 00:10:56,320
'Offer your prayers',

129
00:10:56,320 --> 00:10:58,326
'Beseech the Lord'.

130
00:10:58,516 --> 00:11:00,520
You're hiding something from me, aren't you?

131
00:11:00,520 --> 00:11:01,906
Good Lord!

132
00:11:01,906 --> 00:11:04,331
It seems you'd tear up any moment!

133
00:11:04,331 --> 00:11:07,029
Didn't I just say it's nothing, really?

134
00:11:07,029 --> 00:11:08,700
Mum had said once,

135
00:11:08,700 --> 00:11:09,720
'You offer prayers'

136
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:11,212
'And beseech the Lord'

137
00:11:11,212 --> 00:11:14,946
'The moment you have the slightest of doubt'.

138
00:12:17,140 --> 00:12:18,821
What is going on?

139
00:12:18,821 --> 00:12:20,939
Nothing, really...

140
00:12:20,939 --> 00:12:24,822
We're both scared, so, for a while,

141
00:12:24,822 --> 00:12:26,870
